'''Franck Yannick Kessié''' (born 19 December 1996) is an Ivorian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder|central]] [[midfielder]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al-Ahli Saudi FC|Al-Ahli]] and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team.]]

After advancing through [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]], Kessié joined [[AC Milan]] in 2017 on loan, securing a permanent move two years later and playing a pivotal role in their [[Serie A]] success in the 2021–22 season. In 2022, he joined [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], clinching titles in [[La Liga]] and [[Supercopa de España]], before his transfer to Al-Ahli in 2023.

An Ivorian international since 2014, Kessié was part of the squad that won the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] on home soil.

== Club career ==
Born in [[Ouragahio]], Kessié began his career in [[Stella Club d'Adjamé]], joining their youth setup in 2010.<ref name="outsideoftheboot.com">{{cite web|url=http://outsideoftheboot.com/2017/04/30/scout-report-franck-kessie/|title=Charles Onwuakpa writes a detailed scout report about Franck Kessié|publisher=outsideoftheboot.com|date=15 April 2017|access-date=26 May 2019|archive-date=18 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220518134152/http://outsideoftheboot.com/2017/04/30/scout-report-franck-kessie/|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2014, he was promoted to the first team.<ref name="outsideoftheboot.com" />

=== Atalanta ===
On 29 January 2015, Kessié signed a three-year contract with [[Serie A]] club [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.afrik-foot.com/stella-club-kessie-signe-a-l-atalanta-bergame|title=Stella Club: Kessié signe à l'Atalanta Bergame|trans-title=Stella Club: Kessié signs with Atalanta Bergamo|publisher=Afrik-Foot|language=fr|date=30 January 2015|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170326135543/http://www.afrik-foot.com/stella-club-kessie-signe-a-l-atalanta-bergame|archive-date=26 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was assigned to the club's [[Atalanta B.C. Primavera|Primavera]] squad upon his arrival and contributed with seven appearances for the side. His first match in Europe occurred on 1 March, as he started in a 2–0 away win against [[A.C. Milan Primavera|AC Milan Primavera]].{{citation needed|date=August 2017}}

On 18 April 2015, Kessié was called up to the first team for a match against [[A.S. Roma|Roma]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.calcionews24.com/atalanta-22-convocati-per-roma-prima-per-kessie-437342|title=Atalanta, 22 convocati per Roma: prima per Kessie|trans-title=Atalanta, 22 called up for Roma: first for Kessie|publisher=Calcio News 24|language=it|date=18 April 2015|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517141758/http://www.calcionews24.com/atalanta-22-convocati-per-roma-prima-per-kessie-437342|archive-date=17 May 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> but remained an unused [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in the 1–1 draw the following day.

==== Cesena (loan) ====
On 26 August 2015, Kessié joined [[A.C. Cesena|Cesena]] in the [[Serie B]] on a one-year loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cesenacalcio.it/it/news/2015/08/26/kessie-%C3%A8-un-giocatore-del-cesena-3706.html|title=Kessie è un giocatore del Cesena|trans-title=Kessie is a Cesena player|publisher=A.C. Cesena|language=it|date=26 August 2015|access-date=26 May 2016|archive-date=4 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304071132/http://www.cesenacalcio.it/it/news/2015/08/26/kessie-%C3%A8-un-giocatore-del-cesena-3706.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his professional debut on 26 September, coming on as a substitute for [[Antonino Ragusa]] in a 0–0 away draw against [[A.C. Perugia Calcio|Perugia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.umbriaon.it/perugia-cesena-0-0-ecco-la-diretta/|title=Perugia–Cesena 0–0, tensioni dopo la gara|trans-title=Perugia–Cesena 0–0, tension after the match|publisher=Umbria On|language=it|date=26 September 2015|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517095140/http://www.umbriaon.it/perugia-cesena-0-0-ecco-la-diretta/|archive-date=17 May 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Kessié scored his first professional goal on 31 October 2015, netting the last in a 2–0 home win against [[S.S. Virtus Lanciano 1924|Virtus Lanciano]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ilcentro.gelocal.it/sport/2015/10/31/news/torna-la-difesa-titolare-per-fermare-il-cesena-1.12362905|title=Il Lanciano gioca bene ma perde a Cesena per 2 a 0|trans-title=Lanciano play well but lose to Cesena by 2–0|publisher=Il Centro|language=it|date=31 October 2015|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-date=26 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170326051307/http://ilcentro.gelocal.it/sport/2015/10/31/news/torna-la-difesa-titolare-per-fermare-il-cesena-1.12362905|url-status=dead}}</ref> He became an undisputed starter afterwards, appearing in 37 matches and scoring four goals as his side missed out promotion in [[2015–16 Serie B#Promotion play-offs|the play-offs]].

==== Return to Atalanta ====
After returning from loan, Kessié was promoted to the first team by manager [[Gian Piero Gasperini]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/calcio/nuove-forze-calcio/18-07-2016/atalanta-gasperini-scopre-kessie-nuovo-yaya-toure-ivoriano-prestito-cesena-centrocampista-160395068337.shtml|title=Atalanta, Gasperini scopre il jolly Kessie, ivoriano che sogna Yaya Touré|trans-title=Atalanta, Gasperini discovers the wildcard Kessie, Ivorian who resembles Yaya Touré|publisher=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|language=it|date=18 July 2016|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-date=17 May 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517101245/http://www.gazzetta.it/calcio/nuove-forze-calcio/18-07-2016/atalanta-gasperini-scopre-kessie-nuovo-yaya-toure-ivoriano-prestito-cesena-centrocampista-160395068337.shtml|url-status=live}}</ref> After appearing with the main squad during the pre-season, he made his debut for ''La Dea'' on 13 August 2016, starting and scoring the last in a 3–0 [[Coppa Italia]] home win against [[U.S. Cremonese|Cremonese]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bergamopost.it/rubriche/l-atalanta-siamo-noi/alla-dea-basta-un-tempo-cremonese-battuta-3-0/|title=Alla Dea basta un tempo: 3–0|trans-title=To ''Dea'' one half is enough: 3–0|publisher=Ecco di Bergamo|language=it|date=14 August 2016|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170326052317/http://www.bergamopost.it/rubriche/l-atalanta-siamo-noi/alla-dea-basta-un-tempo-cremonese-battuta-3-0/|archive-date=26 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> Six days later, he renewed his contract until 2021.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.atalanta.it/site/paginalive/comunicati-dal-club/Stagione-2016-2017/2016-08/19-08-Kessie-sino-al-2021.html|title=Franck Kessie rinnova fino al 30 giugno 2021|trans-title=Franck Kessie renews until 30 June 2021|publisher=Atalanta B.C.|language=it|date=19 August 2016|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170326135828/https://www.atalanta.it/site/paginalive/comunicati-dal-club/Stagione-2016-2017/2016-08/19-08-Kessie-sino-al-2021.html|archive-date=26 March 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Kessié made his debut in the main category of Italian football on 21 August 2016, as he started and scored a brace in a 4–3 home loss against [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/87826|title=Atalanta 3–4 Lazio|publisher=Football Italia|date=21 August 2016|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-date=1 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001062607/https://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/87826|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored another goal seven days later, in a 2–1 away defeat to [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/87842|title=Sampdoria 2–1 Atalanta|publisher=Football Italia|date=28 August 2016|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-date=15 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915075245/https://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/87842|url-status=live}}</ref>

Kessié subsequently became a mainstay in Gasperini's starting eleven, scoring the winners against [[Torino F.C.|Torino]] (2–1 home win)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/87846|title=Atalanta 2–1 Torino|publisher=Football Italia|date=11 September 2016|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-date=30 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830154553/https://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/87846|url-status=live}}</ref> and Roma (2–1 home win),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/87946|title=Atalanta 2–1 Roma|publisher=Football Italia|date=20 November 2016|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-date=30 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830154551/https://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/87946|url-status=live}}</ref> both through [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalties]]. He also scored the equalizer against [[Empoli F.C.|Empoli]] on 20 December 2016, with [[Marco D'Alessandro]] scoring a [[Last-minute goal|last-minute winner]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/87996|title=Atalanta 2–1 Empoli|publisher=Football Italia|date=20 December 2016|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-date=30 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830154531/https://www.football-italia.net/SerieA/match/87996|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== AC Milan ===
On 2 June 2017, Kessié joined fellow Serie A side [[A.C. Milan|AC Milan]] on a two-year loan deal with the obligation to buy.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Official: Kessie is now red and black |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/official-statement/2017-06-02/official-kessie-is-now-red-and-black |publisher=A.C. Milan Official Site |date=2 June 2017 |access-date=2 June 2017 |archive-date=17 June 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170617121550/https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/official-statement/2017-06-02/official-kessie-is-now-red-and-black |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40136347|title=Ivory Coast's Franck Kessie joins AC Milan from Atalanta|date=2 June 2017|publisher=BBC Sport|access-date=27 August 2019|archive-date=30 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830154522/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40136347|url-status=live}}</ref> Originally, he chose 19 as his [[Squad number (association football)|shirt number]] but soon was persuaded by the club's management to leave it for [[Leonardo Bonucci]], who transferred to Milan a few weeks later; as a result, Kessié changed it to 79.

He made his debut for Milan and helped the club to win the first leg of Europa League qualification match against [[CS Universitatea Craiova|CS U Craiova]] on 27 July.<ref>{{cite news|title=Newcomers Ricardo Rodriguez, Franck Kessie lift Milan past FC U Craiova|url=http://www.espnfc.com/club/ac-milan/103/blog/post/3166878/newcomers-ricardo-rodriguez-franck-kessie-lift-milan-past-universitatea-craiova|access-date=28 July 2017|work=ESPN|date=27 July 2017|archive-date=30 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830130450/http://www.espnfc.com/club/ac-milan/103/blog/post/3166878/newcomers-ricardo-rodriguez-franck-kessie-lift-milan-past-universitatea-craiova|url-status=live}}</ref> On 20 August 2017, in Milan's opening Serie A match of the season, he scored a penalty in a 3–0 victory over [[F.C. Crotone|Crotone]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Kessie, Cutrone, Suso in form as Milan begins Serie A campaign with win |url=http://www.espnfc.com/club/ac-milan/103/blog/post/3184887/ac-milan-make-easy-work-of-serie-a-opener-winning-at-crotone |publisher=ESPN |date=20 August 2017 |access-date=29 August 2017}}</ref> In a match against [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] on 21 January 2018, Kessié scored two goals, one being from the penalty spot, to give Milan the win.<ref>{{cite web |title=Cagliari 1-2 Milan: Kessie double inspires comeback win |url=https://sempremilan.com/cagliari-1-2-milan-kessie-double-inspires-comeback-win |website=sempremilan |date=21 January 2018 |access-date=18 February 2022 |archive-date=18 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220218194615/https://sempremilan.com/cagliari-1-2-milan-kessie-double-inspires-comeback-win |url-status=live }}</ref> Milan reached the Coppa Italia final, but lost 4–0 to Juventus, Kessié playing the full game. Following Bonucci's departure he was offered his original shirt number back yet refused, citing that he did not want to force Milan fans to spend any extra money on his personalized shirts due to yet another number change.<ref>{{cite web |date=14 February 2019 |title=AC Milan, Kessie: 'Gasperini is angrier than Gattuso!' |url=https://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/ac-milan-kessie-gasperini-is-angrier-than-gattuso-80241 |publisher=www.calciomercato.com |access-date=15 February 2019 |archive-date=15 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190215115352/https://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/ac-milan-kessie-gasperini-is-angrier-than-gattuso-80241 |url-status=live }}</ref> As Juventus won the league-cup double, Milan qualified for the [[2018 Supercoppa Italiana]] final against Juventus. They lost 1-0 and Kessié was sent off in the 74th minute.<ref>{{cite news |title=Juventus beat Milan to Supercoppa Italiana after Cristiano Ronaldo winner |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jan/16/juventus-milan-cristiano-ronaldo-supercoppa-italiana |access-date=18 February 2022 |agency=The Guardian |date=16 January 2019 |archive-date=3 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221103135647/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jan/16/juventus-milan-cristiano-ronaldo-supercoppa-italiana |url-status=live }}</ref>

Milan finished the [[2020–21 Serie A]] season in second place, with Kessié scoring 13 times in 37 appearances, and qualified for the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League]] after an eight-year absence.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-italia.net/171087/atalanta-0-2-milan-kessie-seals-second-place |title=Atalanta 0-2 Milan: Kessie seals second place |website=football-italia.net |date=23 May 2021 }}</ref>
Kessie became the first player to score at least ten penalties for AC Milan in a Serie A season since [[Zlatan Ibrahimovic]] in 2011–12; he played 50 matches this season in all competitions, a record between Serie A players with [[Matteo Politano|Politano]],<ref>{{cite web |title=ATALANTA V AC MILAN: THE NUMBERS FROM THE GAME |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/stats/2021-05-23/atalanta-v-ac-milan-the-numbers-from-the-game |website=acmilan |access-date=18 February 2022 |archive-date=10 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220210233044/https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/stats/2021-05-23/atalanta-v-ac-milan-the-numbers-from-the-game |url-status=live }}</ref> and was described as player of the season for Milan by some critics.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pickering |first1=Joe |title=Franck Kessié: Milan's player of the year? |url=https://milanreports.com/2021/05/31/kessie-player-of-the-year/ |website=MILAN REPORTS |date=31 May 2021 |access-date=18 February 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Burns |first1=Euan |title=A SEASON IN REVIEW: AC MILAN 2020/21 |date=8 June 2021 |url=https://forzaitalianfootball.com/2021/06/a-season-in-review-ac-milan-2020-21/ |access-date=18 February 2022}}</ref>

==== 2021–22: Scudetto winner and departure ====
On 12 September 2021 against Lazio, Kessié won a penalty kick but failed to convert it; Milan still managed to win the match 2–0.<ref>{{cite web |title=AC MILAN MAKE IT THREE WINS FROM THREE |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/serie-a/2021-09-12/ac-milan-make-it-three-wins-from-three |website=acmilan |access-date=19 February 2022}}</ref> On 28 September, in a UEFA Champions League match against [[Atlético Madrid]], as Milan was leading by 1–0, Kessié was sent off in the 29th minute, his side eventually lost 1–2.<ref>{{cite news |title=AC Milan 1–2 Atletico Madrid |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58705891 |access-date=18 February 2022 |archive-date=18 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220218191052/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58705891 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 31 October against Roma, he converted a penalty kick to score the second and seal a 2–1 victory for Milan.<ref>{{cite web |title=THREE BIG POINTS IN THE CAPITAL |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/serie-a/2021-10-31/three-big-points-in-the-capital |website=acmilan |access-date=18 February 2022 |archive-date=18 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220218194904/https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/serie-a/2021-10-31/three-big-points-in-the-capital |url-status=live }}</ref> On 7 November, while playing [[Derby della Madonnina|against Inter]] he fouled [[Hakan Çalhanoğlu]] in the penalty box, causing a penalty kick which the latter scored in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite news |title=Soccer-Milan and Inter share spoils in derby thriller |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-italy-mil-int-report-idUKKBN2HS0I7 |access-date=18 February 2022 |work=Reuters |date=8 November 2021 |archive-date=18 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220218191754/https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-italy-mil-int-report-idUKKBN2HS0I7 |url-status=live }}</ref>
On 4 December, Kessié scored the first goal against Salernitana in an eventual 2–0 win.<ref>{{cite web |title=AC MILAN V SALERNITANA: THE STATS FROM THE GAME |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/stats/2021-12-04/ac-milan-v-salernitana-the-stats-from-the-game |website=acmilan |access-date=19 February 2022 |archive-date=19 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220219064200/https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/stats/2021-12-04/ac-milan-v-salernitana-the-stats-from-the-game |url-status=live }}</ref>
On 22 December, Kessié scored a brace against [[Empoli F.C.|Empoli]], reaching 14 Serie A goals during the 2021 calendar year; the last AC Milan midfielder to score so much in a single calendar year was [[Kaká]] in 2008.<ref>{{cite web |title=EMPOLI V AC MILAN: THE NUMBERS FROM THE GAME |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/stats/2021-12-22/empoli-v-ac-milan-the-numbers-from-the-game |website=acmilan |access-date=18 February 2022 |archive-date=27 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221127020432/https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/stats/2021-12-22/empoli-v-ac-milan-the-numbers-from-the-game |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 22 May 2022, Kessié scored the third goal in a 3–0 rout against Sassuolo, sealing the [[Scudetto]] title for the club; after the goal, Kessié went to Milan fans at the [[Mapei Stadium – Città del Tricolore|Mapei Stadium]] and did his trademark salute, it was Kessié's last match and goal with Milan, as he announced his departure a few days later and thanked the fans.<ref>{{cite web |title=Barcelona-Bound Kessié: "No Better Way to Leave Milan" |url=https://cultofcalcio.com/barcelona-bound-kessie-no-better-way-to-say-goodbye-to-milan/?amp=1 |website=cult of calcio|access-date=22 May 2022}}</ref>

=== Barcelona ===
On 4 July 2022, [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] announced that they had reached an agreement with Kessié after his contract expires with [[AC Milan]] and on 6 July, he signed a four-year deal until 30 June 2026, and his buy out was set at €500m.<ref>{{Cite web |title=FC Barcelona sign Franck Kessie |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2666705/fc-barcelona-sign-franck-kessie |access-date=2022-07-04 |website=www.fcbarcelona.com |language=en |archive-date=4 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220704145341/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/2666705/fc-barcelona-sign-franck-kessie |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 13 August 2022, he made his debut for the club, as a substitute to [[Pedri]], in a 0–0 draw against [[Rayo Vallecano]] in the league.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 August 2022 |title=Barcelona frustrated by Rayo Vallecano as Lewandowski & Raphinha's La Liga debuts spoiled |url=https://www.goal.com/en-in/news/barcelona-frustrated-rayo-vallecano-opening-night/bltcd5e7b01eea1ab09 |access-date=16 August 2022 |language=en |archive-date=16 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220816104641/https://www.goal.com/en-in/news/barcelona-frustrated-rayo-vallecano-opening-night/bltcd5e7b01eea1ab09 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 19 March 2023, Kessié scored the winning goal against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] in ''[[El Clasico]]'', his first for the club, hitting home [[Alejandro Balde]]'s cutback in the 92nd minute to make it 2–1 for the ''Blaugrana''.<ref>{{Cite web |title=FC Barcelona – Real Madrid La Liga Matchday 26 |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/matches/78066/fc-barcelona-r-madrid-la-liga-2022-2023 |access-date=2023-03-21 |website=www.fcbarcelona.com |language=en}}</ref> Kessié's strike was the 3,000th goal scored by Barcelona at the [[Camp Nou]] in [[La Liga]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kessie scores goal number 3,000 at Spotify Camp Nou in La Liga |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3116980/kessie-scores-goal-number-3000-at-spotify-camp-nou-in-la-liga |access-date=2023-03-21 |website=www.fcbarcelona.com |language=en |archive-date=20 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230320185418/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3116980/kessie-scores-goal-number-3000-at-spotify-camp-nou-in-la-liga |url-status=live }}</ref>

=== Al-Ahli ===
On 9 August 2023, Kessié joined [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Ahli Saudi FC|Al-Ahli]] in a €12.5m deal.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kessie transfer to Al-Ahli SC agreed |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3621056/kessie-transfer-to-al-ahli-sc-agreed |publisher=[[FC Barcelona]] |access-date=9 August 2023 |date=9 August 2023 |archive-date=9 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230809205304/https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/3621056/kessie-transfer-to-al-ahli-sc-agreed |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club in a 1–0 win over [[Al-Okhdood Club|Al-Okhdood]] on 24 August. Kessié also scored another winning goal in a 1–0 win over [[Al-Khaleej FC|Al-Khaleej]] on 29 December.

During the [[2024–25 AFC Champions League Elite]] on 16 September 2024, Kessié scored the only goal in the match against Iranian club [[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]] to secured the 3 points for Al-Ahli. In the final match held in Jeddah on 3 May 2025, he won the competition, after previously scoring a goal in the 42nd minute when defeating the Japanese representative, [[Kawasaki Frontale]].<ref name=":02">{{Cite web |last=Lynch |first=Joey |date=3 May 2025 |title=Never taking their eyes off the prize, Al Ahli are champions of Asia at long last |url=https://global.espn.com/football/story/_/id/44984369/never-taking-eyes-prize-al-ahli-champions-asia-long-last |access-date=4 May 2025 |website=ESPN}}</ref> In the following season, he was named the Most Valuable Player in the [[2025–26 AFC Champions League Elite]] as his club secured a 1–0 extra-time victory over [[FC Machida Zelvia|Machida Zelvia]] in the [[2026 AFC Champions League Elite final|final]].<ref name="afc26">{{cite web |url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/club/afc_champions_league_elite.html/news/al-ahli%E2%80%99s-kessie-named-most-valuable-player |title=Al Ahli's Kessie named Most Valuable Player |publisher=The AFC |date=25 April 2026 }}</ref>

== International career ==

=== Youth ===
Kessié represented [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]] at [[Ivory Coast national under-17 football team|under-17]] and [[Ivory Coast national under-20 football team|under-20 levels]], appearing in the [[2013 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] and [[2015 Toulon Tournament]]. During the former tournament, the [[Royal Moroccan Football Federation]] submitted a complaint to [[FIFA]] claiming that Kessié was aged 22 and not 16;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espoirsdufootball.com/cm-u17-scandale-franck-kessie-16-ans-aurait-22-ans-31003|title=CM U17 – Scandale, Franck Kessié (16 ans) aurait 22 ans|trans-title=U17 WC – Scandal, Franck Kessié (16 years) 22 years old|publisher=Espoirs du Football|language=fr|date=30 October 2013|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170603010318/http://www.espoirsdufootball.com/cm-u17-scandale-franck-kessie-16-ans-aurait-22-ans-31003|archive-date=3 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> FIFA later denied that claim.

=== Senior ===
At the age of 17, Kessié played his first international game with the senior national team on 6 September 2014, starting in a 2–1 home win against [[Sierra Leone national football team|Sierra Leone]] for the [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gh/news/4351/africa/2014/09/06/5088565/cote-divoire-2-1-sierra-leone-the-elephants-toil-to-overturn|title=Cote D'Ivoire 2–1 Sierra Leone: The Elephants toil to overturn lead|publisher=Goal.com|date=6 September 2014|access-date=8 September 2014|archive-date=3 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220503204552/https://www.goal.com/en-gh/news/4351/africa/2014/09/06/5088565/cote-divoire-2-1-sierra-leone-the-elephants-toil-to-overturn|url-status=live}}</ref> On 4 January 2017, he was included in [[Michel Dussuyer]]'s 23-man squad ahead of the [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/38451141|title=Afcon 2017: Wilfried Zaha in Ivory Coast's final squad|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=4 January 2017|access-date=25 March 2017|archive-date=2 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190802000846/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/38451141|url-status=live}}</ref> starting in all matches as his side was knocked out in the group stage.

At the [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations]], he finished as the joint-top assist provider of the tournament, alongside [[Ismaël Bennacer]], with three assists. His team were eliminated in the quarter-finals by eventual champions [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] after losing 4–3 on penalties following a 1–1 draw on 11 July; Kessié converted his nation's first penalty in the shoot-out.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://futaa.com/article/188128/top-assists-charts-at-the-2019-african-cup-of-nations |title=Top Assists charts at the 2019 African Cup of Nations |publisher=futaa.com |last1=Otieno |first1=Imran |date=20 July 2019 |access-date=4 August 2019 |archive-date=3 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220503204545/https://futaa.com/article/188128/top-assists-charts-at-the-2019-african-cup-of-nations |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cafonline.com/total-africa-cup-of-nations/matches/47/ |title=Côte d'Ivoire 1-1 Algeria |publisher=www.cafonline.com |date=11 July 2019 |access-date=4 August 2019 |archive-date=30 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330202738/https://www.cafonline.com/total-africa-cup-of-nations/matches/47/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jul/19/senegal-algeria-africa-cup-of-nations-final-match-report|title=Algeria claim second Afcon title after Bounedjah's lucky strike sinks Senegal|website=theguardian.com|publisher=Guardian News & Media Limited|date=19 July 2019|access-date=19 July 2019|archive-date=20 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190720130642/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jul/19/senegal-algeria-africa-cup-of-nations-final-match-report|url-status=live}}</ref>

Kessié started in all four of the Ivory Coast's matches at the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/team/squad/_/id/4789/league/CAF.NATIONS/season/2021|title=Ivory Coast Squad|access-date=16 January 2024|website=ESPN|archive-date=16 January 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240116135914/https://www.espn.com/soccer/team/squad/_/id/4789/league/CAF.NATIONS/season/2021|url-status=live}}</ref> scoring once in a 3–1 win over Algeria in [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations Group E|Group E]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/59975483|title=Afcon 2021: Holders Algeria crash out after Ivory Coast defeat|date=20 January 2022|access-date=16 January 2024|website=ESPN|archive-date=28 January 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220128134139/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/59975483|url-status=live}}</ref> He was substituted with an injury 30 minutes into the round of 16 loss to [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://supersport.com/football/wta/news/23b19666-cddd-4098-b1f8-193fa240f797/egypt-defeat-elephants-on-penalties-to-book-quarters-berth|title=Egypt defeat Elephants on penalties to book quarters berth|date=27 January 2022|access-date=16 January 2024|website=SuperSport|archive-date=12 December 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241212184324/https://supersport.com/football/wta/news/23b19666-cddd-4098-b1f8-193fa240f797/egypt-defeat-elephants-on-penalties-to-book-quarters-berth|url-status=live}}</ref>

In December 2023, Kessié was named in the Ivory Coast's squad for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/federationivoiriennedefootball/posts/pfbid02GVkTYXjhv2yBQizHRNxngTGoMrFLXgcUg3kQeXgEk3gZ158w6cxqRFjDBXCCU3ihl|title=LA LISTE|publisher=[[Ivorian Football Federation]]|date=28 December 2023|access-date=16 January 2024|language=pt|via=[[Facebook]]|archive-date=28 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231228204941/https://www.facebook.com/federationivoiriennedefootball/posts/pfbid02GVkTYXjhv2yBQizHRNxngTGoMrFLXgcUg3kQeXgEk3gZ158w6cxqRFjDBXCCU3ihl|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/media/ow2obxrw/c%C3%B4te-divoire.pdf|title=CÔTE D'IVOIRE|publisher=Confederation of African Football|date=5 January 2024|access-date=16 January 2024|archive-date=13 February 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240213160033/https://www.cafonline.com/media/ow2obxrw/c%C3%B4te-divoire.pdf|url-status=live}}</ref> He captained the team in the tournament's opening match, a 2–0 win over [[Guinea-Bissau national football team|Guinea-Bissau]] on 14 January 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2024/1/14/afcon-ivory-coast-vs-guinea-bissau-africa-cup-of-nations-2023|title=Ivory Coast open AFCON 2023 with 2-0 win over Guinea-Bissau|date=14 January 2024|access-date=16 January 2024|website=Al Jazeera}}</ref> During the round of 16 match against defending champions [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]], he came off the bench in the second half, in which he managed to score the equalizer from a penalty in the 86th minute in a 1–1 tie. He eventually netted the last penalty in the shoot-outs in a 5–4 win, which qualified his country to the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/jan/29/kessie-brings-ivory-coast-back-to-life-as-afcon-hosts-bury-senegal |title=Kessié brings Ivory Coast back to life as Afcon hosts bury Senegal |work=The Guardian |date=30 January 2024 }}</ref> He later scored a goal in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations final|final]] match against [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] which ended in a 2–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68196261 |title=Nigeria 1–2 Ivory Coast |publisher=BBC Sport |date=11 February 2024 |access-date=11 February 2024 |archive-date=12 February 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240212182429/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68196261 |url-status=live }}</ref>

Kessié later became the captain of his national team in 2024, succeeding [[Max-Alain Gradel]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.africatopsports.com/2024/03/23/cote-divoire-max-alain-gradel-dit-elephants/ |title=Côte d'Ivoire : Max-Alain Gradel dit au revoir aux Eléphants |publisher=Africa Top Sports |language=fr |date=23 March 2024 }}</ref> On 6 January 2026, he made his 100th international appearance in a 3–0 win over [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso]] during the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]] round of 16.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/football/match/_/gameId/732176/burkina-faso-ivory-coast |title=Ivory Coast 3–0 Burkina Faso |publisher=ESPN |date=6 January 2026 }}</ref>

On May 15, 2026, Kessié was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Faé]] in his list of 26 players in order to participate in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

== Personal life ==
When Kessié was 11 years old, his father, who used to be a professional footballer in his youth before enlisting in the Ivorian army, died due to an illness. Therefore, one of his goal celebrations is a [[military salute]] performed in order to pay tribute to his late father.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/it/notizie/milan-kessie-e-lesultanza-da-militare-una-dedica-al-padre/1brwxoeypry9u12vjtw5yo804w|title=MILAN, KESSIÉ E L'ESULTANZA DA MILITARE: UNA DEDICA AL PADRE|trans-title=MILAN, KESSIÉ AND THE MILITARY GESTURE: A DEDICATION TO FATHER|publisher=Goal|date=21 September 2017|access-date=22 September 2017|archive-date=22 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170922194540/http://www.goal.com/it/notizie/milan-kessie-e-lesultanza-da-militare-una-dedica-al-padre/1brwxoeypry9u12vjtw5yo804w|url-status=live}}</ref> Growing up, his idol was [[Yaya Touré]].<ref>{{Citation |title=WHO IS YOUR IDOL? {{!}} KESSIE FACES THE #90SECONDSCHALLENGE |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eDug8l_9_DY&t=61s |language=en |access-date=2022-09-07}}</ref>

Kessié is a practicing Muslim.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Gaudiano |first=Gabriella |date=2022-04-08 |title=Milan, Kessie e Bennacer alle prese col Ramadan: il piano per gestirli |url=https://www.milanlive.it/2022/04/08/milan-kessie-e-bennacer-alle-prese-col-ramadan-il-piano-per-gestirli/ |access-date=2023-10-05 |website=Milanlive.it |language=it-IT |archive-date=18 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231018092334/https://www.milanlive.it/2022/04/08/milan-kessie-e-bennacer-alle-prese-col-ramadan-il-piano-per-gestirli/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=D'Avino |first=Giovanni |date=2022-04-08 |title=C'è il Ramadan: programma alimentare ad hoc e tanto riposo per Bennacer e Kessie – MilanPress |url=https://www.milanpress.it/ramadan-bennacer-e-kessie/ |access-date=2023-10-05 |language=it-IT |archive-date=18 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231018092333/https://www.milanpress.it/ramadan-bennacer-e-kessie/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Mzoughi |first=Wajih |date=2022-04-08 |title=In occasion of Ramadan, AC Milan arranges special programme for its muslim players |url=https://milanreports.com/2022/04/08/ac-milan-ramadan-programme/ |access-date=2023-10-05 |website=Milan Reports |language=en-GB |archive-date=18 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231018092333/https://milanreports.com/2022/04/08/ac-milan-ramadan-programme/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He regularly fasts during the Islamic month of [[Ramadan]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ferrara |first=Chiara |date=2021-04-14 |title=Ramadan al via: ecco i giocatori di Serie A a digiuno |url=https://sport.meteoweek.com/2021/04/14/ramadan-al-via-ecco-i-giocatori-di-serie-a-a-digiuno/ |access-date=2023-10-05 |website=Sport Meteoweek |language=it-IT |archive-date=18 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231018092332/https://sport.meteoweek.com/2021/04/14/ramadan-al-via-ecco-i-giocatori-di-serie-a-a-digiuno/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Fisher |first=Oliver |date=2022-04-08 |title=GdS: Kessie and Bennacer observing Ramadan – Milan's plan to help them |url=https://sempremilan.com/kessie-bennacer-ramadan-milan-plan-help |access-date=2023-10-05 |website=SempreMilancom |language=en |archive-date=18 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231018092332/https://sempremilan.com/kessie-bennacer-ramadan-milan-plan-help |url-status=live }}</ref>

